From Subject On Off Road Rally Joliet ATTENTION ALL FOUR WHEEL OFF ROAD ENTHUSIASTS On Off Road Rally Sunday April Joliet Illinois The Event The Joliet Mud Turtles a Chicago land four wheel drive club is sponsoring an On Off Road Rally Sunday April For those who ask What is an on off road rally An On Off Road Rally consists of the following An on the road rally where participants are given a set of directions and clues guiding participates around the Joliet Plainfield The object is to navigate a course based on a set of directions and Participants will be given a set of questions pertaining to the course which they must answer along the Points are awarded for the number of correct answers Directions will ultimately lead to an off road area where a four wheel drive course is set At various locations in the on road course check points will be set up where participants will be asked other questions or requested to perform some activity tire roll truck tow basketball free throw for additional An optional off road four wheel drive course where participants will navigate off road trails mud bogs and or hill Points are awarded for successfully navigating off road obstacles without getting If you should get stuck which is half the fun anyway there will be assistance to get your vehicle unstuck so you can try it The off road course will divided up based on tire size so stock as well as modified can run the At the end of the rally trophies will be awarded to top scoring Door prizes and dash plaques will also be given Food and drinks also available at the This is an organized activity sponsored by the Joliet Mud Turtles so safety and fun is our foremost All must be street legal and have solid tow points for the off road section of the course we don't want to have to separate someone's bumper from their vehicle The Particulars Rally begins at Instant Replay Plainfield Road Joliet see map below Registration is between and First truck out at Rally date is Sunday April rain or shine There is an entry fee of per You must have a co driver passengers allowed A valid drivers license is required Suggested equipment CB Radio Compass Tow Strap and Clevis Clip Board and Pencil No alcohol during rally For more information contact Gary Tom Norm Brian Instant Replay mi North Exit Canton Larkin Farm Ave v Exit